What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Non-Phthalate Plasticizers Market?

Market Analysis and Size

In the non-phthalate plasticizers market, primary plasticizers (high solvation) such as adipates and trimellitates offer excellent compatibility with polymers, ensuring optimal flexibility and durability. Secondary plasticizers (low solvation) such as benzoates and citrates provide supplementary plasticizing effects and enhance specific properties without compromising overall performance. Together, these categories cater to diverse application needs, ensuring the production of safe and sustainable plastic products.

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the global non-phthalate plasticizers market is expected to reach USD 1,470.95 million by 2031, which was USD 929.89 million in 2023, registering a CAGR of 5.9% during the forecast period of 2024 to 2031. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include in-depth expert analysis, geographically represented company-wise production and capacity, network layouts of distributors and partners, detailed and updated price trend analysis and deficit analysis of supply chain and demand.

